article.description: Nate Navigato and Jaelan Sanford scored 21 points apiece, Marreon Jackson added 15 with nine assists, and Toledo beat Western Michigan 85-77 on Saturday to end a two-game skid.
article.headline: Toledo beats W. Michigan 85-77 behind Navigato, Sanford
article.linkText: Toledo beats W. Michigan 85-77 behind Navigato, Sanford
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- Nate Navigato and Jaelan Sanford scored 21 points apiece, Marreon Jackson added 15 with nine assists, and Toledo beat Western Michigan 85-77 on Saturday to end a two-game skid. Luke Knapke scored 10 and grabbed nine rebounds for the Rockets (13-3, 1-2 Mid-American Conference), who made 14 of 27 3-pointers, led by Navigato's five. Western Michigan led 68-67 after nine lead changes on Kawanise Wilkins' free throw with 4:33 left before Navigato's 3 put the Rockets up for good, 70-68, sparking a 12-2 run. The Broncos closed to six on Jared Printy's layup with 15 seconds left, but got no closer. Willie Jackson's layup put Toledo up 37-36 at halftime after six lead changes. Michael Flowers scored 21 points with seven rebounds and seven assists for the Broncos (6-10, 0-3), who have lost three straight. Seth Dugan had 16 points with 12 rebounds, Printy added 14 points and Josh Davis 13.
